> Hello, Conrad and greetings from a spring-time South Africa! 
> 
> We were told in our mechanical appreticeship to simply calculate the 
> screw/bolt diameter by 0.8! This would give you the core-hole. 
> 
> So, by example, a 6mm bolt has a hole drilled of 4,8mm...a 5mm srew/bolt has 
> an inner diameter of 4.0mm 
> 
> I still find this very helpful, if you would have a broken off srew and want 
> to drill it out... 
> 
> Enjoy your weekend! 
